  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3568979277" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3568979277" />
    <a title="Bhaskar Thakuria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15611888-bhaskar-thakuria"><img alt="Bhaskar Thakuria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1630000871p2/15611888.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3568979277?book_show_action=true">Sep 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bhaskar Thakuria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bhaskar Thakuria" href="/user/show/15611888-bhaskar-thakuria">Bhaskar Thakuria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141185248" href="/book/show/716381.Strait_is_the_Gate">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15611888-bhaskar-thakuria?shelf=french-literature">french-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15611888-bhaskar-thakuria?shelf=20th-century-classics">20th-century-classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15611888-bhaskar-thakuria?shelf=european-literature">european-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15611888-bhaskar-thakuria?shelf=penguin-classics">penguin-classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3568979277" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17061462633050687148"><i>Alas! I understand now only too well; between God and him there is no other obstacle but myself. If perhaps, as he says, his love for me at first inclined him to God, now that very love hinders him; he lingers with me, prefers me, and I am become the idol that keeps him back from making further progress in virtue. One of us two must needs attain to it; and as I despair of overcoming the love in my coward heart, grant me, my God, vouchsafe me strength to teach him to love me no longer, so that at</i></span>
  <span id="freeText17061462633050687148" style="display:none"><i>Alas! I understand now only too well; between God and him there is no other obstacle but myself. If perhaps, as he says, his love for me at first inclined him to God, now that very love hinders him; he lingers with me, prefers me, and I am become the idol that keeps him back from making further progress in virtue. One of us two must needs attain to it; and as I despair of overcoming the love in my coward heart, grant me, my God, vouchsafe me strength to teach him to love me no longer, so that at the cost of my merits I may bring Thee his, which are so infinitely preferable... and if today my soul sobs with grief at losing him, do I not lose him to find him again hereafter in Thee?<br /> Tell me, oh, my God! what soul ever deserved Thee more? Was he not born for something better than to love me? And should I love him so much if he were to stop short at myself? How much all that might become heroic dwindles in the midst of happiness!</i><br /><br />Gide's vision of love is of a heroic ideal, of an idyll that is irreconcilable with the frantic nature of physical urges, of an unbroken yearning that is timeless and transcends several lives and periods. The love between Jerome and Alissa is above the sensual realm of earthly pleasures, and indeed is an ideal that is scarcely recognized in modern society. Alissa is prepared to sacrifice her love for Jerome is endangering his soul and preventing it from getting closer to the heavenly ideal. Her real intent later on is to let Jerome find his true virtue and in which he would be able to transcend and overcome the spirit of the commonplace and the mundane. How many sacrifices of this sort do we see in current society?<br /><br /><i>‘Enter ye in at the strait gate: for wide is the gate and broad is the way that leadeth to destruction, and many there be which go in thereat. Because strait is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it.’</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="17061462633050687148" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


