              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17112544717907746763">A novel about the obsessive devotion of the young Jerome for his niece Alissa. Of course a very delicate theme, considering the time this was written, but Gide has succeeded in bringing it in an interesting and balanced way. <br/>Nice contrast between the monologue of the storyteller and the diary fragments: the latter shows that they still had feelings for each other and daily fought against them. Sobering picture of the repressive culture of religion.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


